                <section id="hello">
                    <h2>Stress V/S Anxiety</h2>
                    <p>Most of the people think that stress and anxiety are the same terms or they use it interchangeably. However, this is not correct; stress and anxiety are not the same terms. Yes, to a some extent they are same but not completely.</p>
                    <h3>Difference between stress and anxiety</h3>
                    <p> In general, stress happens for a short term but anxiety happens for a long term. If the condition or situation, which was giving us, stress (stressor) passes away and we stop thinking about that, then the situation will be of stress. However, even after the stressor passes away, we still over think about a situation continuously with negative thoughts, then this are anxiety. Anxiety causes excessive worries.</p>
                    <p>The three symptoms that are common in stress and anxiety are sleeping problems, fatigue and muscle aches and headaches.</p>
                </section>
